cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI 

The paper discusses a new algorithm for classification in general metric spaces, which is a topic related to machine learning and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the algorithmic core of the approach is based on approximate solutions to classical problems. The paper also mentions experimental evidence of its superiority to some common kernel methods, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the generalization performance of the algorithm, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
